articles.author: Lori Ann LaRocco
articles.title: Red Sea supply chain inflation may be peaking already, new trade data suggests - CNBC
articles.description: Shippers around the world are pushing back on increases from ocean carriers diverting from the Suez Canal, but for U.S.-bound cargo, costs are still rising.
articles.content: The sharp, sudden spike in supply chain inflation caused by the Red Sea crisis and ongoing attacks on shipping vessels by Houthi rebels may have peaked on key global trade routes, based on analysis o… [+6002 chars]
